name: How to register to vote
summary: Election registration deadlines are approaching, and several news articles provide guidance on voter registration for the upcoming elections. In Montana, residents can still register to vote online or by mail, and the deadline is the day before the election. Illinois offers same-day voter registration at polling places, while in Wisconsin, voters can register at the polls on Election Day. Tennessee requires voter registration by mail or in person 30 days before the election. Louisiana does not allow same-day voter registration. New U.S. citizens can register to vote through naturalization or by meeting other eligibility requirements. Additionally, some states, including those mentioned by Axios, allow voter registration at polling places during early voting and Election Day. It's important to note that voter registration deadlines and requirements may vary by state, so it's recommended to check local election websites or contact the appropriate authorities for the most up-to-date information.

name: Quincy Jones
summary: Music icon Quincy Jones, renowned for his collaborations with legendary artists including Frank Sinatra and Michael Jackson, passed away at 91. Jones, recognized as a giant of American music by The New York Times, is hailed for his exceptional leadership skills, ability to foster collaboration, and effortless coolness, as noted by Forbes. The Los Angeles Times highlights his influential role in shaping Michael Jackson's solo career. NPR provides an in-depth look at Jones's life and contributions. Stevie Wonder's heartfelt tribute in Rolling Stone underscores their close bond. Variety acknowledges Jones's Grammy-winning collaborations with Jackson and his work as a film composer. The Seattle Times explores the profound impact of Jones on the city. Pitchfork and Reuters pay homage to Jones's legacy as a music legend who reshaped pop music.

name: Joe Rogan
summary: In a series of recent interviews on the "Joe Rogan Experience" podcast, Joe Rogan sparked controversy and garnered significant attention. Rogan baselessly claimed YouTube suppressed a Trump interview and interviewed J.D. Vance, sparking outrage and discussion. Rogan also endorsed Trump on the eve of the election, leading to widespread media attention. Additionally, Rogan discussed the possibility of interviewing Kamala Harris, even though he rejected her conditions, and showed unedited footage of Trump to millions of viewers. Various news outlets have summarized takeaways and key moments from these interviews, highlighting their impact on public discourse and the political landscape.

name: Whos winning in the polls
summary: According to various polls, the 2024 presidential election between Kamala Harris and Donald Trump is expected to be close. In a poll conducted by the Des Moines Register, Harris has taken the lead in Iowa, while polls by The New York Times and CNN indicate that Harris holds a narrow advantage in Michigan and Wisconsin, but remains tied with Trump in Pennsylvania. A PBS News/NPR/Marist poll also suggests a narrow lead for Harris, while a forecast by Nate Silver for Forbes predicts a virtual tie with Harris closing the gap. Despite the tight race, voters remain divided on whether Harris intends to fulfill her campaign promises, according to an NPR poll. The exact results of the election will not be known until Election Day, with varying predictions on when the winner will be announced.
